## ðŸŽ¨ Styling Guidelines

### Always Include Dark Mode
Every component must support dark mode using Tailwind's `dark:` prefix:

```vue
<div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-100">
```

### Use Theme Colors
Reference colors from [src/config/theme.js](mdc:src/config/theme.js):

```vue
<!-- Primary colors -->
<div class="bg-primary-500 text-primary-600">
<div class="bg-primary-100 dark:bg-primary-900/30">

<!-- Secondary colors -->
<div class="bg-secondary-500 text-secondary-600">

<!-- Accent colors -->
<div class="bg-accent-500 text-accent-600">
```

### Consistent Spacing
- Use `p-6` for card padding
- Use `mb-6` for section margins
- Use `gap-6` for grid/flex gaps
- Use `space-y-6` for vertical spacing

### Consistent Shadows
- Use `shadow-soft` for cards
- Use `shadow-soft-md` for elevated elements
- Use `shadow-soft-lg` for modals

## ðŸ”§ Component Patterns

### Form Components
All form components should:
- Support `v-model` with `modelValue` prop and `update:modelValue` emit
- Include `label`, `required`, `placeholder` props
- Support dark mode
- Include proper focus states

### Button Components
Use [src/components/BaseButton.vue](mdc:src/components/BaseButton.vue) with variants:
- `primary` - Main actions
- `secondary` - Secondary actions  
- `outline` - Cancel/back actions
- `danger` - Delete actions
- `warning` - Edit actions
- `accent` - CTA actions

### Modal Components
Use [src/components/ConfirmModal.vue](mdc:src/components/ConfirmModal.vue) for confirmations:
- `danger` - Delete confirmations
- `warning` - Logout/edit confirmations
- `info` - Information
- `success` - Success messages

